OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FWorld War Two Easter egg   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffrom 1939 set for auction  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, An 84-year-old chocolate egg that      
OL,6, survived wartime unbroken and uneaten  
OL,7, is being auctioned in May.             
OL,9,FThe egg was given to nine-year-old     
OL,10,FSybil Cook from Neath for Easter in    
OL,11,F1939.                                  
OL,13,FWith war clouds looming, her uncle     
OL,14,Fadvised her to ration it and savour    
OL,15,Fevery morsel.                          
OL,17,FDespite loving chocolate, she did not  
OL,18,Fjust ration it, but dutifully kept and 
OL,19,Ftreasured it for her whole life, until 
OL,20,Fshe died in 2021.                      
